Normalcy has returned to Mambilla Plateau in Sardauna local government area of Taraba state where dozens of people were killed in attacks on Fulani communities by suspected militia. Daily Trust gathered that the return of peace in the troubled area followed deployment of hundreds of soldiers and police as well as peace initiative by the state government. It was further gathered that the state government has brought elders and elite from both Mambilla and Fulani for a roundtable and peace accord. Elders from both sides have agreed to call their people to order. The deputy governor Alhaji Haruna Many had also led a team comprising representatives of Fulani and Mambilla to towns and villages attacked on the Plateau and preached peace. Daily Trust gathered that this was the first time elite and key political figures from both sides would be brought together and made to talk to their people on peace.